Reasoning: The paper focuses on developing a context-aware model for predicting engagement of elderly care, which involves the use of IoT and personalized services. This suggests a strong emphasis on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The proposed model also involves the use of topic modeling, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of scalability and composite relationships, which may involve the use of complex systems (cs.SI).
